Hello all,

You’re probably familiar with our admin Amber, affectionately known to her friends as Yams. Amber is an incredibly caring and special person who pours her all into her hobbies, convictions, and her friendships. Whenever something happens, she’s the first to jump in determining how to help others. This rings especially true in her efforts to support peers in emergencies, and her work fostering pups for the Humane Society.

Today, Amber needs our help. She was injured in a tragic accident and is presently in the hospital. So we’re reaching out to the communities she’s spent many years putting love into, in the hopes that we can help her now.

Thank you for your time in reading this, and thank you if you choose to give. Anything helps.

gofundme.com

Hello Dogspotters,

Roe V Wade was overturned in the U.S.. While trying to think of a good way to put this, I think I’ll just end up quoting Bungie’s statement on Twitter. “Standing up for reproductive choice and liberty is not a difficult decision to make, and [we] remain dedicated to upholding these values.” Our stance on this matter remains firm - we support human rights and wish to uplift the voices of the millions of folks impacted by these developments.

That said, as we have asked for in the past on other important matters, posts regarding this subject must include original content of a dog spot, and we ask that self promotional content and content promoting unrelated agendas be omitted. Thank you, happy spotting, and please don't lose hope.

Hey spotters, as most of you know there are tragic events presently unfolding in Ukraine.

Though we work to keep Dogspotting free of political issues, we have always stood up for human rights. We will not allow posts arguing about politics, however, on this thread we will allow posts of support.

We have always tried to remain a positive place where people can go to escape the difficulties of every day life and it is our full intention to continue to do so.

Here are some links with resources for folks that need it. Feel free to share any REPUTABLE information for other organizations and charities that we missed, and watch out for misleading content and organizations.

https://ukrainewar.carrd.co/

And most of all we encourage everyone to be excellent and compassionate to one another ❤️

🚨Hi Everyone🚨

Please post pics of your pets in the comments so as many members as possible see this.

As you are all aware, there are a variety of ongoing natural disasters, including Hurricane Ida, and the wildfires and floods affecting multiple states. We’ve compiled a list of disaster relief organizations accepting donations towards those affected, and are sharing it with y’all here. We are also inviting y’all to share additional aid organizations we may have missed. Please feel free to link them below in the comments – but if you do so, please be certain the resource you’re sharing is authentic. We’ll do our best to keep this list updated.

💲The Red Cross is fundraising.

https://www.redcross.org/

💲Direct Relief is fundraising.

https://www.directrelief.org/2021/08/as-hurricane-ida-gains-strength-over-caribbean-u-s-gulf-coast-prepares-for-impact/

https://www.facebook.com/172286261142/posts/10157946114491143/

https://bvspca.org/hurricane-ida/

Happy New Year, spotters! We have an exciting update for everyone

This past year has been a difficult one for everyone, and like many others, we wanted to ring in the new year with a fresh start. What this means for the group is an awesome new points system!
Many from the last iteration of bonus points remain, but we’ve added some new ones and brought back some old favorites. We’ve created an instructional Powerpoint for everyone to learn about these changes, as well as a handy cheat sheet to take with you as you spot!
Feel free to post your own dog or a favorite spot in the comments and let us know which new bonus point is your favorite!

  ·   ·
Hi everyone. We keep Dogspotting free of political issues but what is happening now goes beyond political views, it is an issue of human rights. The Dogspotting team stands behind the movement and ideal that Black Lives Matter. This is not a policy up for debate.

This being said, we have always wanted this to be a place to escape from the trouble of the outside. Right now that means a place that people can exist without being reminded of the fear of death.

Having said that, your post must remain within the other guidelines; adding something related to BLM at the bottom of a rule breaking post does NOT mean we will leave it up.

We encourage positive dog related content that supports Black Lives Matter, but please leave antagonistic arguments at the door.

(More info: https://blacklivesmatters.carrd.co/)
blacklivesmatters.carrd.co
